content.description: Start low and right with a LH undercling and RH on arete. Make a strong move to a thin sharp crimp on the slab and slap out left. Continue up and left to top out.
content.protection: Pads and spotter. Cover the pit under the boulder.
content.location: Bottom of the Mirror Talus Field. Hike the railroad tracks till you see the telephone pole with the "172" sign. Enter there and head up and right staying towards the bottom tree line of the field.

content.description: Start sitting matched on an obvious edge (same start as Lying Leadership). Bust big left to an incredible sloper then finish up the slab.  The left most line on the little 3 boulder.
content.location: Little three boulder, which is right next to trash panda.  Low in talus just in the trees along tree line at the bottom of the field.  The twins are 150/200 feet south.

content.description: Center line on little 3 boulder.  Start matched on edge from a sit.  One way or another get the jug up and right and finish up the slab.
content.location: On little three boulder right next to Trash Panda.

content.description: From a sit, left hand on a ledge and right on a low sidepull, climb the short arete.  The right most line on the little 3 boulder.
content.location: On little three boulder.  Right next to Trash Panda.  Bottom of Mirror talus just in trees.  Easiest to enter from the north.

content.description: Trash Panda boulder and the neighboring Little 3 boulder are in the edge of the woods, near the lower (north) end of the boulder field.
